              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "incident_source": [
                  "D-T"
                ],
                "reaction": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                "      H3(d,n)He4 reaction. Neutron yield about",
                "10**9 n/S in 4pi"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Metal-     Li-7 isotope in metallic form evaporated on",
                "a gold foil. Sample thickness about 1 millig/sqcm"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The charged particle spectra were measured using a",
                " ((delta-E)/(delta-x))-E counter telescope, the neutron",
                "yield was monitored by counting the associated alpha",
                "particle."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TELES"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                "    counter telescope composed of two differen-",
                "tial-E gas proportional counters and one E-counter",
                "which could be a CsI scintillator or a surface barrier",
                "detector. Angular resolution about 8 degrees(at 20 deg)"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Angular distribution compared with DWBA prediction for",
                "the pick-up of two nucleons. Deduced spectroscopic",
                "factors for He-5 and He-6"
              ]
            }
          ],
